WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.327 --> 00:00:30.126
Argh!

2
00:00:34.167 --> 00:00:36.193
Argh!

3
00:00:38.705 --> 00:00:39.968
Help!

4
00:00:41.275 --> 00:00:45.838
Get the beast out before
it cleaves me in two!

5
00:00:51.885 --> 00:00:55.754
Get your bastard hands inside
me and tug the bugger free!

6
00:00:55.956 --> 00:00:57.254
Fetch Treves.

7
00:01:02.996 --> 00:01:04.294
Chloroform. now!

8
00:01:04.498 --> 00:01:05.830
Which nimgimmer's this. then?

9
00:01:06.033 --> 00:01:08.093
The one who's to
cut you open. woman.

10
00:02:17.004 --> 00:02:20.941
Please. sir. he's
mine. I beg you!

11
00:02:21.575 --> 00:02:24.067
Please do not take him from me!

12
00:02:31.118 --> 00:02:34.111
Morning porter found her. at
the foot of the Eastern Stair.

13
00:02:34.388 --> 00:02:36.254
She came to you when?

14
00:02:36.456 --> 00:02:39.290
A touch after
eight this night last.

15
00:02:39.459 --> 00:02:43.453
as I prepared my testimony for
the Linklater enquiry. She was filthy.

16
00:02:44.197 --> 00:02:45.790
Cursed like a stevedore.

17
00:02:46.633 --> 00:02:50.434
Her son delivered by Caesar
one hour later and now removed.

18
00:02:50.637 --> 00:02:53.368
We know not where. Or by whom.

19
00:02:53.573 --> 00:02:56.566
Whoever pushed her down
that stairwell. I should think.

20
00:02:56.777 --> 00:02:59.042
With a mother now
dead. poor child.

21
00:02:59.246 --> 00:03:01.272
vulnerable does not
quite cover it. Inspector.

22
00:03:01.481 --> 00:03:02.505
No belongings?

23
00:03:02.716 --> 00:03:04.912
Nothing to say her name
or who might miss her now?

24
00:03:05.118 --> 00:03:06.416
None.

25
00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:09.784
Then she goes to my
American at Leman Street.

26
00:03:10.157 --> 00:03:12.456
One last thing you should see.

27
00:03:15.362 --> 00:03:17.354
Sergeant. help me turn her.

28
00:03:18.565 --> 00:03:20.261
It may help identify her.

29
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:32.937
Oh. blimey.

30
00:04:29.236 --> 00:04:31.205
Who's to say you
are not beautiful?

31
00:04:33.673 --> 00:04:34.902
Wilson!

32
00:04:35.675 --> 00:04:39.510
Jedediah Shine lays his
sergeant in earth this morning.

33
00:04:39.780 --> 00:04:42.579
Needs must. our
respects are paid.

34
00:04:48.355 --> 00:04:50.085
It is yet to be stated
how. precisely.

35
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.282
Sergeant Linklater met his end.

36
00:04:52.492 --> 00:04:55.223
Granted. the iron railing that
passed through him had a say.

37
00:04:55.428 --> 00:04:57.624
But there are whisperings
on the wind. Wilson.

38
00:04:57.831 --> 00:05:01.791
our dear friend Edmund Reid may
have lent a shoulder to that passing.

39
00:05:03.670 --> 00:05:05.161
Talk of the wolf.

40
00:05:07.541 --> 00:05:09.100
How now. Inspector?

41
00:05:11.912 --> 00:05:14.381
Such an injury. Mr Reid.

42
00:05:15.715 --> 00:05:16.876
It changes a man.

43
00:05:17.551 --> 00:05:18.780
Humbles him. in fact.

44
00:05:20.453 --> 00:05:21.921
Humble Fred Best.

45
00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:26.592
I wonder how it is you
show your faces here.

46
00:05:30.697 --> 00:05:31.697
He was my friend.

47
00:05:33.867 --> 00:05:36.496
And yet you are happy to
remain at the side of a man

48
00:05:37.137 --> 00:05:40.164
whose hand is suspected in
that friend's own timely demise?

49
00:05:40.373 --> 00:05:43.639
You ought to be careful. Mr
Shine. making such statements.

50
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:45.642
How. Sergeant?

51
00:05:46.112 --> 00:05:49.947
Fellas might ask. what's
to be gained from slurring

52
00:05:50.150 --> 00:05:52.176
the reputation of a
man such as Mr Reid.

53
00:05:52.385 --> 00:05:53.385
Yeah. indeed.

54
00:05:53.553 --> 00:05:55.749
- And that slur hides the truth.
- Whose?

55
00:05:55.956 --> 00:06:00.417
Yours! Inspector. Your
activities in this division.

56
00:06:01.595 --> 00:06:02.756
Wilson!

57
00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:05.764
You are a disgrace
to badge and uniform.

58
00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:10.526
It is your inspector here that is the
disgrace. and you would slur me?

59
00:06:10.737 --> 00:06:12.035
Then I must seek recompense.

60
00:06:12.239 --> 00:06:13.298
Then seek it. sir!

61
00:06:13.506 --> 00:06:15.372
Word had it you'd
left the roped ring.

62
00:06:15.575 --> 00:06:16.575
Word has it right.

63
00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:20.340
Well. then. I confess myself
relieved that you have not

64
00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:23.712
grown entirely soft...

65
00:06:23.917 --> 00:06:26.580
on your whore
wife's perjury of love.

66
00:06:26.786 --> 00:06:29.312
No. Not here. Not now.

67
00:06:29.522 --> 00:06:35.587
But soon. Sergeant. Once the world
has heard Mr Treves sworn testament

68
00:06:37.764 --> 00:06:40.563
and knows Inspector
Reid for the killer he is.

69
00:06:49.943 --> 00:06:51.741
Bruising and breakage
to the hip. pelvis.

70
00:06:51.945 --> 00:06:57.248
knee and back. Her humerus.
radius and ulna. however. are intact.

71
00:06:57.450 --> 00:06:59.248
She didn't use her
arms to break the fall.

72
00:06:59.452 --> 00:07:01.216
She kept the child
clutched to her chest.

73
00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:02.650
She died to protect it.

74
00:07:02.856 --> 00:07:04.654
A mother's instinct.

75
00:07:04.858 --> 00:07:06.224
Gone to nothing.

76
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:09.487
Treves described her as
filthy and abject. didn't he?

77
00:07:11.197 --> 00:07:13.928
But I think she is beautiful.

78
00:07:14.134 --> 00:07:17.127
And whoever cared for
her thought the same.

79
00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:22.474
Torn and distressed. However.
the stitching is highly skilled...

80
00:07:22.676 --> 00:07:24.838
These threads.
stolen most likely.

81
00:07:25.045 --> 00:07:27.207
Tell me. did she
steal her skin as well?

82
00:07:29.416 --> 00:07:32.853
See her face -zinc oxide.
It keeps the skin fair.

83
00:07:33.053 --> 00:07:34.214
Kept well for a while.

84
00:07:34.421 --> 00:07:36.185
Oh. she was kept perfect.

85
00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:44.856
And yet. no attempt was
made to remove... that from her.

86
00:07:45.065 --> 00:07:47.330
You think that makes her.
what? Less than human?

87
00:07:47.534 --> 00:07:49.969
We were all animals
once. it is now said.

88
00:07:50.170 --> 00:07:52.071
Some more closely
related than others.

89
00:07:52.272 --> 00:07:53.797
I would. in conscience.

90
00:07:54.007 --> 00:07:58.468
leave off riding Sergeant Drake.
He has buried a friend today.

91
00:07:58.912 --> 00:08:01.404
Blessed though she may
be. this woman was murdered

92
00:08:01.614 --> 00:08:03.173
and her child taken.

93
00:08:03.383 --> 00:08:04.908
This tail is a vestige.

94
00:08:05.118 --> 00:08:07.280
It is a memento of
all that we once were.

95
00:08:08.989 --> 00:08:11.117
In water. beneath the canopy.

96
00:08:12.959 --> 00:08:13.517
Sergeant Drake.

97
00:08:13.927 --> 00:08:16.396
The freak shows were run
off the street fronts last year.

98
00:08:16.596 --> 00:08:19.657
but there was talk. was there not.
of Tom Norman's troop splintering.

99
00:08:19.866 --> 00:08:21.528
a faction returning
from Nottingham?

100
00:08:21.735 --> 00:08:25.035
Hidden away under the
railway arches. up on Artillery.

101
00:08:29.909 --> 00:08:31.537
Chief Inspector Abberline.

102
00:08:31.745 --> 00:08:32.745
Inspector Reid.

103
00:08:34.114 --> 00:08:35.707
Reinforcements.

104
00:08:46.826 --> 00:08:51.355
He's a boy. I said... I
asked... Not another boy.

105
00:08:51.564 --> 00:08:57.026
Sergeant? You are short here. I
am correct in that understanding?

106
00:08:57.237 --> 00:08:58.364
You are.

107
00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:03.173
He is. We are. sir.

108
00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:06.835
You believe there to be a
line outside my office. do you?

109
00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:10.745
A battalion of gnarled veterans.
each and every one of them

110
00:09:10.950 --> 00:09:13.215
begging to bring their
fight to your division?

111
00:09:13.420 --> 00:09:14.444
Light. friend? This one.

112
00:09:14.654 --> 00:09:16.953
Detective Constable Flight -

113
00:09:17.157 --> 00:09:22.152
worked overtime in uniform
on his own coin. his collar rate

114
00:09:22.362 --> 00:09:26.197
in so doing sufficient to push
both yours and mine into the corner.

115
00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:28.425
In Bloomsbury. Fred.

116
00:09:28.868 --> 00:09:32.862
And now appointed to the
CID. He wishes to work here.

117
00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:37.067
He volunteers for this sink.
Edmund. For Whitechapel.

118
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:49.049
Inspector Reid. It is an
honour. I shan't let you down. sir.

119
00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:52.881
Easily said. Constable.
Harder to prove.

120
00:09:54.327 --> 00:09:56.262
Inspector. private word?

121
00:10:00.066 --> 00:10:02.194
Little birdie hopped
on my shoulder earlier.

122
00:10:02.402 --> 00:10:05.031
Told me a story about
a ruckus at a funeral.

123
00:10:05.238 --> 00:10:07.366
That birdie currently
sporting a tea cup for an ear?

124
00:10:07.574 --> 00:10:09.042
Oi! You two!

125
00:10:09.242 --> 00:10:12.144
If Drake cannot keep
his spleen inside him.

126
00:10:13.346 --> 00:10:15.781
it is up to you to
provide discipline.

127
00:10:17.417 --> 00:10:17.907
Oi!

128
00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:20.019
Sergeant Linklater
was his friend.

129
00:10:20.253 --> 00:10:22.449
And Jedediah
Shine is his superior.

130
00:10:22.655 --> 00:10:25.215
And if that superior merits
such insubordination.

131
00:10:25.825 --> 00:10:27.293
merits worse than that. perhaps?

132
00:10:27.527 --> 00:10:29.086
No. You leave be.

133
00:10:29.295 --> 00:10:31.992
It's not as if your name is
currently being sung from the

134
00:10:32.198 --> 00:10:34.929
rooftops with the
acme of probity.

135
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:39.869
And should Treves not clear you
at that inquest. so it will remain.

136
00:10:40.273 --> 00:10:43.243
You are my friend. but. Ed -

137
00:10:43.543 --> 00:10:50.040
you make accusations against a
man of such standing without evidence.

138
00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:56.884
No. You hear me?
Inspector? Am I heard?

139
00:11:02.729 --> 00:11:04.288
To Artillery.

140
00:11:09.569 --> 00:11:12.903
All men of ambition need a
trade to fall back on. Miss Hart.

141
00:11:13.106 --> 00:11:17.373
A skill. which keeps
both body and soul apiece

142
00:11:17.577 --> 00:11:19.739
when the wind of
fortune turns cold.

143
00:11:19.946 --> 00:11:23.542
So I'm glad to see you're not
broken by our new terms. Miss Hart.

144
00:11:31.491 --> 00:11:32.823
You do not wish to count it?

145
00:11:33.026 --> 00:11:36.963
We are friends. And
friends do not break trust.

146
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:41.528
Or forget their
obligations to each other.

147
00:11:45.171 --> 00:11:50.474
Obligations which. should you
need reminder. might be forgot.

148
00:11:51.344 --> 00:11:57.011
within just one word and just
one night. If you have my meaning?

149
00:11:57.584 --> 00:11:59.280
If that will be all. Mr Duggan.

150
00:12:01.554 --> 00:12:02.554
Oh.

151
00:12:02.622 --> 00:12:05.251
Do send my regards
to your pistol twister.

152
00:12:05.458 --> 00:12:08.656
You must have him working
those skilled fingers to the knuckle.

153
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:32.613
What ho! Caliban! I say!

154
00:12:34.387 --> 00:12:39.587
Wouldst thou seek to
violate the honour of my child?

155
00:12:39.792 --> 00:12:43.194
I will rack thee. Caliban.

156
00:12:43.429 --> 00:12:49.164
make thee roar that beasts
shall tremble at thy din.

157
00:13:04.717 --> 00:13:06.447
That's enough now.
Sergeant. I think.

158
00:13:06.686 --> 00:13:10.282
Now. now. lady. This
sideshow is now shut down.

159
00:13:10.556 --> 00:13:11.556
On what grounds?

160
00:13:11.691 --> 00:13:14.126
On the grounds of a murder
inquiry. Miss Pettigrew.

161
00:13:14.327 --> 00:13:18.924
Murder and abduction. An infant
boy taken from his murdered mother.

162
00:13:19.399 --> 00:13:22.301
And you believe we can
help you in this because?

163
00:13:22.502 --> 00:13:24.903
She also had a blessing.

164
00:13:25.371 --> 00:13:27.897
A protrusion at the
base of her spine.

165
00:13:29.776 --> 00:13:31.039
A tail?

166
00:13:31.811 --> 00:13:34.610
You must mean Stella Brooks.

167
00:13:36.349 --> 00:13:37.977
Oh. John.

168
00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:43.748
She was found last
night. Mr Goode.

169
00:13:44.190 --> 00:13:45.214
And a child?

170
00:13:48.061 --> 00:13:50.530
You say. her child?

171
00:13:50.997 --> 00:13:53.796
A boy. We believe alive.

172
00:13:55.034 --> 00:13:56.935
- But taken.
- Oh!

173
00:13:57.136 --> 00:13:59.571
When did you last
see her. Mr Goode?

174
00:13:59.772 --> 00:14:03.300
Almost seven
months ago to the day.

175
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:05.239
That is precise recall.

176
00:14:05.445 --> 00:14:08.005
I have been looking for her.

177
00:14:08.214 --> 00:14:09.773
She was what - your lover?

178
00:14:15.822 --> 00:14:18.417
At the hospital. she
was unaccompanied?

179
00:14:18.624 --> 00:14:21.321
Nothing upon her but the
ragged clothes she wore.

180
00:14:21.527 --> 00:14:25.430
But those clothes...
once pretty.

181
00:14:25.631 --> 00:14:27.827
She had been. at one
point at least. well treated.

182
00:14:28.034 --> 00:14:29.366
By folk with money.

183
00:14:29.535 --> 00:14:31.663
Here. brother. Let me
give you something.

184
00:14:31.804 --> 00:14:33.773
There is nothing for me!

185
00:14:46.219 --> 00:14:47.448
Out the way. Haystack.

186
00:14:54.360 --> 00:14:57.455
That man... trussed up as
Caliban. with you. all last night?

187
00:14:57.597 --> 00:15:00.260
He was. And all
here will confirm it.

188
00:15:02.535 --> 00:15:04.731
That's an impressive
artifice you got there.

189
00:15:04.937 --> 00:15:08.066
Oh. it's not artifice.
It's John's gift.

190
00:15:09.509 --> 00:15:14.243
He's impervious to pain.
But not. alas. to suffering.

191
00:15:14.747 --> 00:15:17.444
And Miss Brooks? What of her?

192
00:15:17.650 --> 00:15:22.782
Rootless. Orphaned. Tom Norman
had her displayed in a glass cabinet -

193
00:15:22.989 --> 00:15:24.321
only her rear. mind.

194
00:15:24.524 --> 00:15:28.325
For an extra penny. they could open
the box and a man might tug on her.

195
00:15:28.628 --> 00:15:29.755
And no family?

196
00:15:29.962 --> 00:15:33.330
No friends other than yourselves to
tell who might mean her such harm?

197
00:15:33.733 --> 00:15:38.296
There is a friend. And he
is known to you already. sir.

198
00:15:52.285 --> 00:15:54.845
You must. Joseph.

199
00:15:56.189 --> 00:15:59.159
You must say what you saw.

200
00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:01.887
Come!

201
00:16:03.429 --> 00:16:05.159
Mr Treves.

202
00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:10.469
How can I help you. Inspector?

203
00:16:11.637 --> 00:16:13.697
I'd have you confirm something.

204
00:16:19.445 --> 00:16:20.242
What of it?

205
00:16:20.379 --> 00:16:23.872
In one week. you will stand
in front of a judicial inquiry

206
00:16:24.083 --> 00:16:27.451
and pronounce what took
my sergeant from this life.

207
00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:30.646
I would know now if you
will tell precisely what it was

208
00:16:30.857 --> 00:16:35.557
you witnessed when you came upon
Edmund Reid at my man's bedside.

209
00:16:35.862 --> 00:16:39.629
That is for me to share with
none other than the coroner.

210
00:16:45.238 --> 00:16:46.433
Good day to you.

211
00:16:46.706 --> 00:16:47.867
Good day. Mr Merrick.

212
00:16:52.445 --> 00:16:54.505
You are a good man. sir.

213
00:16:56.916 --> 00:17:01.616
But you have no clue of
the suffering that is meted out

214
00:17:01.821 --> 00:17:03.756
in the Leman Street cells.

215
00:17:04.056 --> 00:17:05.615
Suffering that

216
00:17:06.592 --> 00:17:10.962
Inspector Reid sanctions
in the name of investigation.

217
00:17:13.399 --> 00:17:14.697
Mr Treves?

218
00:17:15.134 --> 00:17:16.134
J... Joseph?

219
00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:19.300
There is a matter urgent.

220
00:17:19.705 --> 00:17:22.903
I believe. which I
would share with you.

221
00:17:23.075 --> 00:17:26.045
Mr Merrick. I don't believe
I have had the pleasure.

222
00:17:31.284 --> 00:17:34.846
I... My... My apologies.

223
00:17:36.622 --> 00:17:39.057
Do not disturb.

224
00:18:06.852 --> 00:18:12.052
Hush now. No panic. Mr
M. No harm is meant here.

225
00:18:12.825 --> 00:18:14.521
Not yet. leastwise.

226
00:18:19.632 --> 00:18:23.364
Please. my supports...

227
00:18:24.337 --> 00:18:26.169
I'm suffocating...

228
00:18:26.505 --> 00:18:28.064
Upsidaisy.

229
00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:32.740
So it is true. then?

230
00:18:34.614 --> 00:18:40.315
You must sleep upright. like a
marionette on a puppeteer's shelf?

231
00:18:43.155 --> 00:18:49.026
This life -six bags of
shit till Sunday. is it not?

232
00:18:49.161 --> 00:18:51.357
And here am I about
to make yours worse.

233
00:18:51.564 --> 00:18:57.435
You see. it strikes me you may have
laid eyes on me some place before.

234
00:18:58.170 --> 00:19:02.369
The night my man
Linklater passed?

235
00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:10.516
No. I... I must have
myself confused.

236
00:19:11.283 --> 00:19:14.117
That is a relief.

237
00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:16.118
Nevertheless...

238
00:19:17.623 --> 00:19:20.252
I hope neither of us
will now forget the other.

239
00:19:22.228 --> 00:19:27.394
Forget how easy it is for me to come
by and say. "How do. Mr Merrick?

240
00:19:27.833 --> 00:19:31.531
"I do hope the day
finds you well. And safe.

241
00:19:31.737 --> 00:19:35.697
"And not inclined to say
nothing you should not."

242
00:19:37.376 --> 00:19:39.368
Are we understood. sir?

243
00:19:53.759 --> 00:19:56.228
Sergeant Artherton.
how do we find Mr Flight?

244
00:19:56.429 --> 00:19:59.365
He is calm. sir. And quiet.

245
00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:01.295
Which is a bonus.

246
00:20:01.467 --> 00:20:03.245
Mr Flight. would you
agree with that assessment?

247
00:20:03.269 --> 00:20:05.135
I would always agree
with my sergeant.

248
00:20:05.304 --> 00:20:07.432
- Oh. biddable. are we?
- Servile. even?

249
00:20:07.673 --> 00:20:09.005
We shall see. For
now. Detective.

250
00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:11.677
let's see how developed your
archive and telegraph skills are.

251
00:20:11.911 --> 00:20:15.040
John Goode. A common enough
name and most uncommon man.

252
00:20:15.247 --> 00:20:16.247
See what you can find.

253
00:20:16.449 --> 00:20:18.884
I want to know why
he would run from us.

254
00:20:19.085 --> 00:20:22.021
Follow me. Up here. son.

255
00:20:22.555 --> 00:20:24.217
Yes. sir.

256
00:20:30.496 --> 00:20:31.828
Mr Merrick.

257
00:20:32.031 --> 00:20:33.090
Mr Merrick...

258
00:20:33.299 --> 00:20:36.701
Detective Inspector Reid.
I'd hoped to talk with you.

259
00:20:38.003 --> 00:20:39.801
Please. I... I am not well.

260
00:20:39.939 --> 00:20:41.805
I have only a few
questions. Mr Merrick.

261
00:20:42.007 --> 00:20:43.999
I have said that I am unwell!!

262
00:20:44.210 --> 00:20:45.735
Sir. sir. sir. sir. sir...

263
00:20:45.945 --> 00:20:51.680
No! You overstep. Inspector. Or
have you no respect for my wishes?

264
00:20:52.218 --> 00:20:52.878
Of course.

265
00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:55.405
But it is a friend of yours
from the side shows... No. sir!

266
00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:58.820
Reid! This is unconscionable!

267
00:20:59.358 --> 00:21:02.157
You will not bring your Leman
Street ways to this hospital again.

268
00:21:02.361 --> 00:21:03.361
- But...
- No. sir.

269
00:21:11.570 --> 00:21:13.402
Joseph. I'm sorry. Joseph.

270
00:21:20.880 --> 00:21:23.372
Does Mr Merrick have
knowledge of her. sir?

271
00:21:23.582 --> 00:21:26.279
If he does. he will
not share it with me.

272
00:21:28.387 --> 00:21:31.915
John Goode's books. That's
some technical reading.

273
00:21:33.025 --> 00:21:36.518
Mr Galton. Mr Galton
is a cousin of Mr Darwin.

274
00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:38.162
This. he investigates

275
00:21:38.397 --> 00:21:40.889
if our abilities might be
inherited from our parents.

276
00:21:41.100 --> 00:21:45.561
and if we. in turn. hand on those
same abilities to our children.

277
00:21:45.838 --> 00:21:48.137
Pugilism. for example.

278
00:21:48.407 --> 00:21:50.433
- Or depravity.
- Quite.

279
00:21:50.709 --> 00:21:56.615
Here. his argument evolves.
He invents a term -eugenics.

280
00:21:56.816 --> 00:21:58.944
Suggests that the qualities
to which we might aspire

281
00:21:59.151 --> 00:22:01.552
could be bred
into the family line.

282
00:22:01.754 --> 00:22:03.222
And what of the weak?

283
00:22:03.422 --> 00:22:07.120
The weak. the idle. the
ugly. the dim-witted. the mad.

284
00:22:07.326 --> 00:22:08.658
The deformed?

285
00:22:08.861 --> 00:22:10.887
They are to be bred out.

286
00:22:20.206 --> 00:22:21.538
Take a seat. Detective.

287
00:22:26.979 --> 00:22:27.979
Drink. Flight?

288
00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:29.080
My thanks. No.

289
00:22:29.215 --> 00:22:31.081
A Mick that doesn't
take a sip. uh?

290
00:22:31.283 --> 00:22:34.344
And a unicorn stopped traffic
on the East India Dock Road.

291
00:22:34.553 --> 00:22:35.987
What do you have. Flight?

292
00:22:36.155 --> 00:22:37.179
John Goode. sir.

293
00:22:37.456 --> 00:22:39.220
- Sit down.
- Not so hard to dig out.

294
00:22:39.425 --> 00:22:41.985
The man has history here.
recent. but history nonetheless.

295
00:22:42.194 --> 00:22:44.288
Fines for drunken
brawling. mainly.

296
00:22:46.165 --> 00:22:49.431
Ropemakers. The Trinity-that's
low-rent boozing. even round here.

297
00:22:49.735 --> 00:22:52.295
The first we know of him here. He
and a woman breaking the peace.

298
00:22:52.471 --> 00:22:53.996
assaulting one
another in the street.

299
00:22:54.406 --> 00:22:56.466
And see her name. Mr Reid...

300
00:22:58.410 --> 00:23:00.003
Stella Brooks.

301
00:23:00.579 --> 00:23:03.947
Nothing before. not a sneeze.
and then September 22nd. this.

302
00:23:04.149 --> 00:23:06.778
Almost precisely seven months
past. When she leaves him.

303
00:23:06.986 --> 00:23:09.114
And his behaviour
degenerating in her absence.

304
00:23:09.321 --> 00:23:10.812
And this the reason
for her leaving?

305
00:23:11.023 --> 00:23:13.492
Did she drop on him the
news that she carried his child?

306
00:23:13.692 --> 00:23:14.921
He didn't exactly rejoice.

307
00:23:15.127 --> 00:23:17.096
They fight. She leaves.
And he hunts her.

308
00:23:17.296 --> 00:23:20.130
He hunts her down
the same streets.

309
00:23:20.332 --> 00:23:24.030
Here - more arrests for
vagrancy. drunkeness.

310
00:23:24.236 --> 00:23:28.367
Ropemakers. Trinity. Thomas
Street. There's pattern to his behaviour.

311
00:23:28.574 --> 00:23:31.066
And so. I thought. Inspector.

312
00:23:31.277 --> 00:23:33.644
if I took a turn through
those streets myself.

313
00:23:33.846 --> 00:23:37.715
I might build an understanding of
him. may indeed pick up his trail.

314
00:23:41.287 --> 00:23:42.516
Then go.

315
00:23:43.122 --> 00:23:44.920
Flight - Drake goes with you.

316
00:23:45.157 --> 00:23:47.092
I'm sure Mrs Drake
expects the sergeant.

317
00:23:47.293 --> 00:23:48.317
He's right. She does.

318
00:23:48.460 --> 00:23:50.759
Take Drake or you're
scrubbing latrines.

319
00:23:52.498 --> 00:23:53.796
Nursemaid. is it?

320
00:23:53.999 --> 00:23:55.365
Just watch him.

321
00:23:57.703 --> 00:23:59.137
You know. Drake or no Drake -

322
00:23:59.338 --> 00:24:02.968
this place is going to shit in
his shoes one day or the next.

323
00:24:03.175 --> 00:24:04.199
He ain't Hobbs.

324
00:24:06.078 --> 00:24:07.512
He ain't.

325
00:24:10.549 --> 00:24:12.347
Will you eat. Captain?

326
00:24:12.551 --> 00:24:15.077
Sorry. Reid. I got. er. I got
dinner with the lady tonight.

327
00:24:15.287 --> 00:24:17.483
Oh. of course. of
course. of course.

328
00:24:25.965 --> 00:24:30.130
The challenge we face.
therefore. those of us who rightly

329
00:24:30.336 --> 00:24:33.500
refuse to accept the
biological status of our species.

330
00:24:33.706 --> 00:24:37.575
is how the debilities
and handicaps

331
00:24:37.776 --> 00:24:45.411
that impair our existence
might be corrected for our heirs.

332
00:24:45.617 --> 00:24:51.318
What is called for. I believe. is
courage. the courage and conviction.

333
00:24:52.524 --> 00:24:59.328
Systematically. to experiment
upon the whole process of breeding.

334
00:24:59.531 --> 00:25:02.365
But not amongst
Sativa or Crustacea.

335
00:25:03.535 --> 00:25:06.027
On complex organisms...

336
00:25:06.238 --> 00:25:10.039
organisms more
like ourselves. in fact.

337
00:25:24.023 --> 00:25:31.692
The correction and improvement
of humankind is indeed realisable.

338
00:25:32.431 --> 00:25:33.490
Thank you.

339
00:25:35.067 --> 00:25:36.091
I say?

340
00:25:37.469 --> 00:25:38.937
Hello. there?

341
00:25:39.571 --> 00:25:43.133
I say. this wing is
research fellows only.

342
00:25:43.675 --> 00:25:44.734
Do I know you?

343
00:25:45.277 --> 00:25:47.269
Oi! Get back here.

344
00:25:54.620 --> 00:25:57.886
Three separate occasions.
he was ejected for brawling.

345
00:25:59.658 --> 00:26:02.753
Only two of us in that
doss-house. We get cornered.

346
00:26:02.961 --> 00:26:04.293
It's a long fight out.

347
00:26:04.496 --> 00:26:06.658
Should we be so
frightened. Sergeant?

348
00:26:09.601 --> 00:26:12.935
Come then. Constable.
I shall show you.

349
00:26:24.116 --> 00:26:25.482
Pretty. ain't it?

350
00:26:27.252 --> 00:26:29.118
John Goode?

351
00:26:33.525 --> 00:26:35.357
I seek a John Goode.

352
00:26:36.528 --> 00:26:38.895
How does one find a
man in such a place?

353
00:26:39.965 --> 00:26:43.629
They are not men no more.
You may not tell 'em apart.

354
00:26:50.075 --> 00:26:52.840
Come. Our luck
is already chanced.

355
00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:57.206
- John Goode?
- Oi!

356
00:26:58.884 --> 00:27:00.045
Devil black spy!

357
00:27:00.319 --> 00:27:01.446
Do you bob from me?

358
00:27:01.753 --> 00:27:03.119
Police. Get back.

359
00:27:03.388 --> 00:27:04.651
- Pigs!
- Bloody fool!

360
00:27:04.823 --> 00:27:05.823
Man: Pigs in the pen.

361
00:27:06.658 --> 00:27:07.658
Back off!

362
00:27:14.566 --> 00:27:18.628
Back! Back off! Run!

363
00:27:19.838 --> 00:27:22.069
Clever fellow. ain't ya?

364
00:27:40.025 --> 00:27:42.290
Tough bugger. ain't you?

365
00:27:45.130 --> 00:27:48.464
Right. Detective
Constable. run along now.

366
00:27:48.667 --> 00:27:50.761
Is there no-one at home
waits for you. Albert?

367
00:27:50.969 --> 00:27:52.494
Not currently. Mrs Drake.

368
00:27:52.704 --> 00:27:54.002
You should call me Bella.

369
00:27:54.206 --> 00:27:56.573
You should call her Mrs Drake.

370
00:27:57.176 --> 00:28:00.840
I lay my head at Mrs Burton's
lodging house on Commercial Street.

371
00:28:01.046 --> 00:28:04.744
Once I am settled. I shall find
more permanent accommodation.

372
00:28:04.950 --> 00:28:07.283
Well. head you home
and get your rest.

373
00:28:08.053 --> 00:28:09.112
Rest. Mrs Drake?

374
00:28:09.721 --> 00:28:12.020
Not this night.
Villainy does not rest.

375
00:28:12.457 --> 00:28:15.757
I do not intend to either. My
thanks. Mrs Drake. Sergeant.

376
00:28:19.031 --> 00:28:20.590
Where did you come from?

377
00:28:20.999 --> 00:28:23.332
Over the hills and far away.

378
00:28:26.405 --> 00:28:29.204
What's stopping
us? Life ain't work.

379
00:28:30.442 --> 00:28:32.638
Cairo. you and me.

380
00:28:33.612 --> 00:28:36.138
Your sergeant's salary
stretches this far. does it?

381
00:28:36.281 --> 00:28:36.748
No.

382
00:28:36.915 --> 00:28:38.960
We're going to take what we've
made here. we're going to cash in...

383
00:28:38.984 --> 00:28:41.749
And what has been made
here. save the names Long Susan

384
00:28:41.954 --> 00:28:44.074
and Captain Jackson?
C'mon. I see the bills you count.

385
00:28:44.156 --> 00:28:46.284
I see the numbers you
scratched in. in that ledger.

386
00:28:46.491 --> 00:28:50.121
Yes. but once counted. you do
not see where those bills leave to.

387
00:28:54.433 --> 00:28:58.700
Nothing here is yours.
Nothing here is mine.

388
00:29:03.375 --> 00:29:05.276
Then whose?

389
00:29:09.114 --> 00:29:13.313
Three years - you never
asked. Never cared.

390
00:29:13.452 --> 00:29:15.546
Hey. you're the one that
wanted to play business-lady

391
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:16.778
and now I'm asking.

392
00:29:19.958 --> 00:29:21.483
Whose is it?

393
00:29:27.199 --> 00:29:28.199
Whose?!

394
00:29:31.136 --> 00:29:32.866
Silas Duggan.

395
00:29:33.505 --> 00:29:38.239
<i>Businesswoman who gives all
the profits away to somebody else.</i>

396
00:29:38.443 --> 00:29:39.968
<i>I wonder why I
didn't think of that!?</i>

397
00:29:40.178 --> 00:29:42.044
I swear to God. you...

398
00:29:42.381 --> 00:29:44.873
are as dead in the
head as this slab of meat!

399
00:29:46.451 --> 00:29:48.352
How could you be so
god damn reckless?

400
00:29:48.553 --> 00:29:50.647
- So. so. so. so god damn...
- What?! What?!

401
00:29:50.856 --> 00:29:52.415
- ..irresponsible!?
- From you!

402
00:29:52.624 --> 00:29:54.559
I mean it. I had
a right to know.

403
00:29:54.760 --> 00:29:59.630
You have no rights. save
the ones you took. for gratis.

404
00:29:59.831 --> 00:30:02.995
each and every night.
in my view and hearing.

405
00:30:03.201 --> 00:30:04.464
Things were different then.

406
00:30:04.670 --> 00:30:07.333
No. The same.

407
00:30:08.573 --> 00:30:14.205
And the same reality prevails.
This place - its people and profits.

408
00:30:14.413 --> 00:30:18.009
The property of... Silas Duggan.

409
00:30:20.686 --> 00:30:25.989
We were destitute.
wanted. criminal.

410
00:30:28.293 --> 00:30:33.823
Not what you would call a sound
investment. Duggan took the chance.

411
00:30:34.032 --> 00:30:41.633
No. What he took was our lives.
Susan. Ground rent plus 50% income.

412
00:30:50.615 --> 00:30:52.413
Any more. Mr Shine?

413
00:30:53.385 --> 00:30:56.184
Sufficient. I think. Mr Duggan.

414
00:30:58.657 --> 00:31:02.458
Barton. good of you to
come when summoned.

415
00:31:02.661 --> 00:31:05.995
I wait on your orders.
Inspector. you know that.

416
00:31:06.932 --> 00:31:09.026
Nothing like loyalty.
is there. Mr Duggan?

417
00:31:09.234 --> 00:31:11.294
Oh. nothing in the
world. Mr Shine.

418
00:31:11.503 --> 00:31:14.371
I'm relieving you of your
everyday duties. Barton.

419
00:31:14.573 --> 00:31:16.906
send you to some surveillance.

420
00:31:17.576 --> 00:31:20.637
Because as we know.
elephants do not forget.

421
00:31:32.124 --> 00:31:33.922
Inspector Reid!
I will not stand.

422
00:31:34.192 --> 00:31:36.320
Mr Merrick. I am well known
to you and I mean no harm.

423
00:31:36.528 --> 00:31:40.590
I come only to enquire
after a friend to you -Stella.

424
00:31:40.866 --> 00:31:43.358
Stella Brooks.
delivered of her child

425
00:31:43.668 --> 00:31:49.403
just hours before she... met her
death here. sir. on these corridors.

426
00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:03.912
When was it you last saw her?

427
00:32:04.089 --> 00:32:07.617
September. L... last year.

428
00:32:07.859 --> 00:32:10.590
After they had fought
and she had left him?

429
00:32:10.762 --> 00:32:11.252
Yes.

430
00:32:11.463 --> 00:32:15.628
And can you say. was it on
account of her pregnancy?

431
00:32:16.268 --> 00:32:19.796
She said she could
not forgive him.

432
00:32:20.138 --> 00:32:21.231
Because he struck her?

433
00:32:21.440 --> 00:32:23.739
No -she could not forgive him

434
00:32:23.942 --> 00:32:29.176
for... for the rage he
felt at the child inside her.

435
00:32:31.817 --> 00:32:35.584
Did she say where it
was she meant to go?

436
00:32:36.288 --> 00:32:39.122
To John's father -a doctor.

437
00:32:39.324 --> 00:32:40.758
And did Goode know this?

438
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:47.627
John had for ever kept his family a
secret from her. his true name also.

439
00:32:47.933 --> 00:32:50.528
The father. a man of wealth.
well able to care for her

440
00:32:50.735 --> 00:32:52.829
and her child - did
she mention a name?

441
00:32:54.206 --> 00:33:01.340
No. she did not. Mr Reid. I
cannot help you further. I...

442
00:33:01.546 --> 00:33:04.778
Mr Merrick. your
help in this matter...

443
00:33:06.251 --> 00:33:08.049
..it is invaluable.

444
00:33:24.803 --> 00:33:27.898
- Been like this all night. they have.
<i>- Your ingratitude is dazzling!</i>

445
00:33:28.039 --> 00:33:31.032
Oh. so I'm supposed to be
grateful for this slave status. huh?

446
00:33:31.243 --> 00:33:33.371
Oh. good morning. Reid.

447
00:33:33.578 --> 00:33:35.240
And. er. what is it
that brings you by?

448
00:33:35.447 --> 00:33:36.915
There's insight
I'd share with you.

449
00:33:37.115 --> 00:33:40.051
So you didn't come
for your shirts then?

450
00:33:40.252 --> 00:33:43.222
Oh. come on - you
truly believe I cannot tell

451
00:33:43.421 --> 00:33:45.720
when another man's shirts
are laundered in my own house?

452
00:33:45.924 --> 00:33:47.984
Although given your head.
you would not have it so

453
00:33:48.193 --> 00:33:50.492
a great deal longer
now. would you?

454
00:33:50.695 --> 00:33:57.260
What? You will not tell your friend
and accomplice? Then allow me.

455
00:33:58.169 --> 00:34:01.697
Your mercenary hireling has
designs on a change of location.

456
00:34:02.073 --> 00:34:04.406
Wishes to up and
leave you. Inspector.

457
00:34:04.609 --> 00:34:06.578
Come on. don't be
such a baby. Reid.

458
00:34:08.513 --> 00:34:10.607
You think this is the
garden spot of the world?

459
00:34:10.815 --> 00:34:13.182
My one ambition to remain
here. chained to you?

460
00:34:13.385 --> 00:34:16.617
Anyway-it's not like I'll be
sailing away any time soon!

461
00:34:18.390 --> 00:34:22.327
You know. this brooding martyr
thing you perfect - it can really grate.

462
00:34:22.928 --> 00:34:25.454
John Goode. Not his real name.

463
00:34:28.199 --> 00:34:28.996
What of him?

464
00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:31.795
A rich man's son. finding
fellowship in a freak show.

465
00:34:32.003 --> 00:34:34.063
- We must ask why.
- The thing with the poker.

466
00:34:34.272 --> 00:34:36.138
It's a skill. not a
handicap. But the palsy...

467
00:34:36.341 --> 00:34:38.970
- The tremor in him.
- So whilst I still may make use of it.

468
00:34:39.177 --> 00:34:42.909
set your great medical
mind to that. will you?

469
00:34:48.887 --> 00:34:50.788
Detective Constable Flight.

470
00:34:51.656 --> 00:34:52.316
Mr Reid.

471
00:34:52.524 --> 00:34:54.604
In the future. you will do
Sergeant Drake the service

472
00:34:54.659 --> 00:34:57.993
of knowing what is best
for you. Will you not?

473
00:34:58.830 --> 00:35:00.059
I will. sir.

474
00:35:00.599 --> 00:35:01.599
Now. speak.

475
00:35:01.866 --> 00:35:05.667
John Goode has been
incarcerated - not in jail. however.

476
00:35:05.870 --> 00:35:07.998
Two spells at The
Lark House Asylum.

477
00:35:08.573 --> 00:35:11.407
Can you speculate
as to which physician?

478
00:35:12.110 --> 00:35:13.110
Karl Crabbe.

479
00:35:13.211 --> 00:35:13.871
The very same.

480
00:35:14.079 --> 00:35:17.015
What tricks did he play
on Mr Goode. I wonder?

481
00:35:41.506 --> 00:35:42.906
Inspector Reid.

482
00:35:43.908 --> 00:35:48.004
A pleasing interruption
to an otherwise dull year.

483
00:35:58.990 --> 00:36:00.288
I forget.

484
00:36:03.628 --> 00:36:07.360
Oh. really. Inspector?
In the current mood?

485
00:36:07.565 --> 00:36:11.195
My mind advances.
but my frame is frail.

486
00:36:11.403 --> 00:36:14.202
How would your newly
sullied reputation cope

487
00:36:14.406 --> 00:36:17.899
with another interview
concluding in a man's death?

488
00:36:18.109 --> 00:36:21.102
Gossip. Reid. It's
a fact of prison life.

489
00:36:24.215 --> 00:36:26.241
Were I to tell you the
life of an infant boy

490
00:36:26.418 --> 00:36:29.081
depended on your speaking.
might that make impact?

491
00:36:30.288 --> 00:36:31.312
Not really.

492
00:36:31.523 --> 00:36:33.788
Then what. Doctor?

493
00:36:37.629 --> 00:36:40.758
There is a tale told. Inspector.

494
00:36:40.965 --> 00:36:44.663
The guards here
tell it. Of your wife.

495
00:36:45.503 --> 00:36:48.735
Rending herself in the
Leman Street gutter.

496
00:36:50.041 --> 00:36:53.409
Sergeant Drake has
heard the tale too. I see.

497
00:36:53.611 --> 00:36:55.842
How difficult for you all.

498
00:36:56.047 --> 00:36:57.174
What is it you want?

499
00:36:57.382 --> 00:37:02.844
To hear it from you. Reid. The
man who brought me so low.

500
00:37:06.825 --> 00:37:08.088
Sergeant Drake.

501
00:37:08.293 --> 00:37:10.194
- Sir?
- Leave us.

502
00:37:10.361 --> 00:37:11.920
- But...
- You heard. Sergeant.

503
00:37:33.685 --> 00:37:36.553
Captain Jackson
found her. In The Bear.

504
00:37:36.921 --> 00:37:40.380
Barely dressed. it is
said. Demanding drink.

505
00:37:40.992 --> 00:37:46.795
He attempted to remove her.
She would not be removed.

506
00:37:47.432 --> 00:37:49.663
And so he carried her.

507
00:37:50.268 --> 00:37:51.793
Which is when she screamed.

508
00:37:52.003 --> 00:37:55.064
<i>In the street. You
tended to her?</i>

509
00:37:55.640 --> 00:37:56.640
I did.

510
00:37:56.908 --> 00:38:00.276
Your sergeant. all
others to bear witness?

511
00:38:03.281 --> 00:38:05.113
And no man to ask you why?

512
00:38:05.316 --> 00:38:07.012
Why such hysteria grew in her.

513
00:38:10.755 --> 00:38:16.626
What cruelty could possibly
merit so public a humiliation?

514
00:38:21.900 --> 00:38:23.801
What did you do
to her. Inspector?

515
00:38:28.740 --> 00:38:30.038
I...

516
00:38:34.045 --> 00:38:35.308
..I lied.

517
00:38:37.182 --> 00:38:38.616
Lied. you say?

518
00:38:41.452 --> 00:38:42.920
On what subject?

519
00:38:44.756 --> 00:38:45.756
Damn you!

520
00:38:55.333 --> 00:38:58.735
I offered her unfair
hope and I deceived her.

521
00:39:00.238 --> 00:39:04.005
I gave her false cause to
believe our lost daughter alive.

522
00:39:04.375 --> 00:39:06.241
And I took another
woman to my bed.

523
00:39:13.985 --> 00:39:15.920
Do you know. Inspector.
of all the emotions.

524
00:39:16.120 --> 00:39:18.954
which is the most
insidious and entrapping?

525
00:39:22.227 --> 00:39:23.388
Shame.

526
00:39:26.164 --> 00:39:30.499
It carves its home in
the marrow of your bones

527
00:39:31.369 --> 00:39:33.895
and rests there for all time.

528
00:39:56.494 --> 00:39:58.725
Where can I find
him? This John Goode.

529
00:39:58.963 --> 00:40:03.298
Whatever he is truly
called. My secrets for his.

530
00:40:05.837 --> 00:40:07.169
A name I cannot give you.

531
00:40:08.673 --> 00:40:11.006
But there is a father.
a doctor. as you know.

532
00:40:11.209 --> 00:40:12.643
And there was a brother.

533
00:40:12.844 --> 00:40:16.372
Both boys subjected to a
regime. a physical regime akin.

534
00:40:16.581 --> 00:40:18.106
you might say. to torture.

535
00:40:18.316 --> 00:40:20.376
Feats of strength insisted upon.

536
00:40:20.585 --> 00:40:23.077
Their bodies stretched from
an early age. beaten with sticks.

537
00:40:23.288 --> 00:40:25.120
bent double.
- But to what end. however?

538
00:40:25.290 --> 00:40:27.486
He could never
articulate it with precision.

539
00:40:27.692 --> 00:40:31.788
Only that he and his
brother shared a curse.

540
00:40:31.996 --> 00:40:36.991
A curse that killed the boys'
mother. A curse of the blood.

541
00:40:37.568 --> 00:40:38.568
And what of the brother?

542
00:40:38.703 --> 00:40:44.301
Drowned himself one morning.
beneath the waters of the Serpentine.

543
00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:47.738
The child you fear for.

544
00:40:47.946 --> 00:40:52.008
if it is Goode's. he will
think it similarly cursed.

545
00:41:05.863 --> 00:41:09.800
A curse of the blood. as Dr
Crabbe would have it. Goode's palsy.

546
00:41:10.001 --> 00:41:11.765
the premature
death of his mother.

547
00:41:11.970 --> 00:41:12.970
An inherited handicap.

548
00:41:13.137 --> 00:41:15.572
Yes. and so -the medical mind?

549
00:41:19.377 --> 00:41:23.542
Huntington's Chorea! Huntington's
Chorea. Slow death sentence. Reid.

550
00:41:23.781 --> 00:41:24.441
What?

551
00:41:24.649 --> 00:41:28.450
The piecemeal loss of all
that makes you feel human.

552
00:41:29.787 --> 00:41:33.724
If either or both of the parents
manifest signs of the disease.

553
00:41:34.025 --> 00:41:36.324
one or more of the offspring
will invariably suffer also.

554
00:41:36.527 --> 00:41:39.691
If. however. those children
manage to go through life

555
00:41:39.897 --> 00:41:42.628
and never manifest.
the thread is broken.

556
00:41:42.834 --> 00:41:43.834
The reason why. then.

557
00:41:43.968 --> 00:41:47.132
this doctor father sought to
make his sons impervious?

558
00:41:47.338 --> 00:41:49.466
To breed out the mutation.

559
00:41:49.674 --> 00:41:52.405
What. then. would he have
made of Miss Brooks' tail?

560
00:41:52.610 --> 00:41:55.079
Perhaps he did not get sight
of it. Not for a good while.

561
00:41:55.380 --> 00:41:57.620
He enjoyed her beauty. until
he claps eyes on her behind.

562
00:41:57.815 --> 00:42:00.182
His disgust sending
her to the streets.

563
00:42:00.385 --> 00:42:03.822
Until... Until he
wonders at his grandson.

564
00:42:04.122 --> 00:42:05.715
at what manner of
man he might become.

565
00:42:05.923 --> 00:42:07.755
And goes to reclaim him.

566
00:42:41.759 --> 00:42:45.628
Five. sir. Five men drowned
in the Serpentine that year.

567
00:42:46.431 --> 00:42:49.299
Corcoran. Robert
Corcoran. age 25.

568
00:42:50.301 --> 00:42:53.465
There is a zoologist
named Corcoran.

569
00:42:53.638 --> 00:42:55.937
He's a... He's a research fellow

570
00:42:56.140 --> 00:42:59.235
at the Natural History
extension of the British Museum.

571
00:43:00.545 --> 00:43:03.014
He concerns himself almost
exclusively with the practical

572
00:43:03.247 --> 00:43:06.775
development of theories first
pronounced by Jean-Baptiste Lamarck.

573
00:43:06.984 --> 00:43:09.852
The biological inheritance
of acquired characteristics.

574
00:43:11.055 --> 00:43:14.082
Our children. Flight. The strength
and skills acquired in this life.

575
00:43:14.292 --> 00:43:17.626
so he proposes. may be handed
down to those who must live the next.

576
00:43:18.262 --> 00:43:20.629
Corcoran is Goode's father.
Corcoran has the child.

577
00:43:21.065 --> 00:43:23.625
Sergeant Drake. a hansom.
We are for South Kensington.

578
00:43:23.868 --> 00:43:25.336
Sir. should I...?

579
00:43:27.705 --> 00:43:29.833
Big boy's game now. son.

580
00:44:03.641 --> 00:44:05.940
Mr. take your mask off.

581
00:44:06.410 --> 00:44:08.845
Go on. take your mask off.

582
00:44:42.680 --> 00:44:45.445
Back! All of you! Back!

583
00:44:48.119 --> 00:44:52.386
Sir. Here. sir. With me.

584
00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:57.051
What is wrong with you?

585
00:44:58.496 --> 00:45:01.432
This man is your fellow!
You would stone him?!

586
00:45:01.666 --> 00:45:02.666
You call him monster?!

587
00:45:02.867 --> 00:45:05.996
Hm? Look on your own sins!

588
00:45:09.073 --> 00:45:11.008
Sir. what is it that's
brought you here?

589
00:45:11.542 --> 00:45:13.135
Inspector Reid.

590
00:45:14.078 --> 00:45:17.913
I... I would speak with him.

591
00:45:18.516 --> 00:45:21.213
I... I believe it urgent.

592
00:45:21.652 --> 00:45:23.348
The Inspector pursues a case.

593
00:45:24.021 --> 00:45:26.456
But I might bring
you to him. sir.

594
00:45:34.098 --> 00:45:35.828
Driver! Step to it.

595
00:45:51.148 --> 00:45:52.912
Alexander.

596
00:45:53.684 --> 00:45:55.448
Hello. Papa.

597
00:45:58.556 --> 00:45:59.717
Is he well?

598
00:45:59.957 --> 00:46:03.450
He is fed and begins to thrive.

599
00:46:04.362 --> 00:46:07.958
And the future? Is
his blood cursed?

600
00:46:08.499 --> 00:46:11.367
Well. the science
is not yet exact.

601
00:46:11.769 --> 00:46:16.139
But the work we performed. you
and I. your strength. Alexander...

602
00:46:17.241 --> 00:46:22.202
My strength. my strength
to absorb your pain.

603
00:46:22.413 --> 00:46:23.745
I made you strong

604
00:46:24.415 --> 00:46:27.112
so that our descendants
might not suffer your curse.

605
00:46:27.652 --> 00:46:29.746
I have hope for this boy.

606
00:46:35.126 --> 00:46:36.890
But none for myself.

607
00:46:39.163 --> 00:46:40.461
Not then. not now.

608
00:46:41.966 --> 00:46:42.966
No.

609
00:46:46.671 --> 00:46:53.544
His mother. Stella. The
day she came to you.

610
00:46:53.811 --> 00:46:59.478
You must have rejoiced
at her? So fine. so strong.

611
00:46:59.817 --> 00:47:05.723
What happened? Did you
finally have full sight of her?

612
00:47:05.923 --> 00:47:07.789
That thing.

613
00:47:08.459 --> 00:47:10.428
We are not so backward as a race

614
00:47:10.628 --> 00:47:12.187
that she could not
have had it removed.

615
00:47:12.430 --> 00:47:14.797
But do you not see. Father?

616
00:47:14.999 --> 00:47:18.458
She had the most
fortunate gift of all.

617
00:47:21.205 --> 00:47:26.303
She felt no shame
for who she was.

618
00:47:28.746 --> 00:47:30.339
And you killed her.

619
00:47:30.614 --> 00:47:33.584
She would not hand him to me.

620
00:47:33.884 --> 00:47:39.824
Slipped. Had she only understood
what was best for the child...

621
00:47:40.024 --> 00:47:43.859
Best for him! What
is best for him?

622
00:47:44.028 --> 00:47:48.625
That he suffer witnessing
your everyday revolution of hope

623
00:47:48.799 --> 00:47:51.132
and despair at his progress?

624
00:47:51.335 --> 00:47:54.066
Or lack of it? Is
that his future?

625
00:47:54.872 --> 00:47:56.033
No.

626
00:47:56.440 --> 00:47:58.432
Best he never knows you.

627
00:48:00.578 --> 00:48:03.104
Or me. Or himself.

628
00:48:03.981 --> 00:48:08.578
Alexander. you hand
that boy back to me!

629
00:48:10.554 --> 00:48:12.955
I am too
well-conditioned. Father.

630
00:48:16.527 --> 00:48:18.655
Alexander. stop!

631
00:48:19.263 --> 00:48:21.425
Alexander! Stop!

632
00:48:23.567 --> 00:48:25.263
Stop!

633
00:48:31.308 --> 00:48:34.278
Alexander. do
not hurt that child!

634
00:48:37.748 --> 00:48:39.842
Alexander!

635
00:48:45.289 --> 00:48:47.815
William Corcoran?
Where is the child?

636
00:48:48.025 --> 00:48:50.290
You are for jail. sir.
Murder and abduction.

637
00:48:50.494 --> 00:48:52.622
I care not for myself. officer.

638
00:48:56.467 --> 00:48:58.663
No! Wait! Mr Goode. wait!

639
00:48:59.670 --> 00:49:02.037
Back! Back. stay back!

640
00:49:02.206 --> 00:49:06.041
Mr Goode. I beg you. I beg
you. Think what you are doing.

641
00:49:06.243 --> 00:49:09.236
I know all too well.

642
00:49:09.447 --> 00:49:11.609
I seek only to reduce

643
00:49:11.882 --> 00:49:16.081
the amount of suffering in
this world. We are cursed!

644
00:49:16.287 --> 00:49:19.951
But sir. I beg you. The child's
fate cannot yet be known.

645
00:49:27.998 --> 00:49:31.594
Please. John! Listen to him!

646
00:49:33.871 --> 00:49:34.600
Joseph?

647
00:49:34.805 --> 00:49:37.900
Mr Reid is known to me. John.

648
00:49:38.108 --> 00:49:42.170
I... I... I... I trust in him.
would... would help him.

649
00:49:42.713 --> 00:49:45.376
Would... would help you.

650
00:49:51.288 --> 00:49:56.659
No-one can help. Joseph.
My brother knew that.

651
00:49:56.861 --> 00:50:00.093
But what of Stella's
wishes for her child?

652
00:50:00.297 --> 00:50:08.297
She is gone. Joseph. and this
child and I. we are left with this truth.

653
00:50:08.873 --> 00:50:14.335
And what is that? That
there is no hope for you?

654
00:50:14.545 --> 00:50:17.515
There is a monster in him.

655
00:50:18.048 --> 00:50:21.541
As surely as there is one in me.

656
00:50:30.928 --> 00:50:34.592
John. look at me. Do it.

657
00:50:35.366 --> 00:50:36.959
Do it!

658
00:50:41.605 --> 00:50:44.575
Am I not monstrous?

659
00:50:47.878 --> 00:50:51.872
It is the truth of my
every waking moment.

660
00:50:52.082 --> 00:50:57.248
And yet. despite
all. I feel joy.

661
00:50:58.188 --> 00:50:59.952
No. I do. I do!

662
00:51:00.157 --> 00:51:06.324
I hear the bells ring from my
room. the chatter of the nurses.

663
00:51:07.531 --> 00:51:10.797
Once. beyond my window.

664
00:51:11.001 --> 00:51:18.704
I... I watched one of their number
make love to the night porter.

665
00:51:19.743 --> 00:51:25.205
I... I... I have never
known that. John.

666
00:51:25.649 --> 00:51:30.246
The... the secret
intimacy of a woman.

667
00:51:30.754 --> 00:51:36.591
that might have told
me I was... desired.

668
00:51:38.395 --> 00:51:41.126
Beautiful in another's eyes.

669
00:51:41.565 --> 00:51:43.761
You. you have known that. John.

670
00:51:45.135 --> 00:51:48.196
Do... do you remember it?

671
00:51:50.240 --> 00:51:51.240
I do.

672
00:51:51.942 --> 00:51:53.911
And what does it feel like?

673
00:51:54.478 --> 00:51:56.276
It felt like peace.

674
00:51:58.816 --> 00:52:06.121
Would you deny your son
that peace. that... that joy?

675
00:52:06.857 --> 00:52:09.417
That... that hope?

676
00:52:12.896 --> 00:52:15.422
It is life. John.

677
00:52:17.368 --> 00:52:18.859
Only life.

678
00:52:20.738 --> 00:52:23.708
What you hold in your arms.

679
00:52:52.636 --> 00:52:58.098
<i>For ever and always. Mr Merrick.
I shall remember you for this.</i>

680
00:52:59.009 --> 00:53:04.414
He is my friend. You
would do no less. Mr Reid.

681
00:53:04.948 --> 00:53:10.182
You put all above yourself.
I know that of you. sir.

682
00:53:11.121 --> 00:53:13.317
You are the best of men.

683
00:53:14.358 --> 00:53:18.159
It is no happy accident
I came to you today.

684
00:53:19.530 --> 00:53:23.194
I... I know not what
the result of this will be.

685
00:53:23.400 --> 00:53:27.770
but there is knowledge
I must share with you.

686
00:53:27.971 --> 00:53:34.036
I... I... I should have said
before. long before. but you see.

687
00:53:34.244 --> 00:53:36.406
I... I saw him.

688
00:53:36.613 --> 00:53:44.544
I... I saw Inspector Shine
murder Sergeant Linklater.

689
00:53:48.358 --> 00:53:50.054
Detective Constable Flight!

690
00:53:50.260 --> 00:53:53.253
You will escort Mr Merrick
back to his rooms at The London.

691
00:53:53.530 --> 00:53:55.692
You remain outside his
door. and allow no man access

692
00:53:55.899 --> 00:53:57.333
unless it is myself.

693
00:53:57.601 --> 00:54:00.298
Yes. sir. Please. Mr
Merrick. Allow me.

694
00:54:08.345 --> 00:54:09.938
With me. Sergeant.

695
00:54:10.147 --> 00:54:12.275
We must bring Chief
Inspector Abberline here

696
00:54:12.483 --> 00:54:14.349
to hear Mr Merrick's testimony.

697
00:55:29.660 --> 00:55:31.219
How do. Mr Merrick.

698
00:55:36.166 --> 00:55:37.998
Why the long face?

699
00:55:39.670 --> 00:55:44.370
Could not do as you
were bid. could you?

700
00:55:44.975 --> 00:55:50.881
Are you not the
brave and noble fellow

701
00:55:52.616 --> 00:55:55.882
and I quite the contrary?

702
00:55:58.188 --> 00:56:04.059
Forced to make a habit of
stealing through these corridors

703
00:56:05.095 --> 00:56:07.496
to end another man's life.

704
00:56:09.233 --> 00:56:13.136
I might almost
resent you for it.

705
00:56:31.021 --> 00:56:33.650
No. no.

706
00:56:35.225 --> 00:56:38.218
Please. please...

707
00:56:41.131 --> 00:56:42.622
What will men say?

708
00:56:46.103 --> 00:56:51.337
The Elephant Man
hoped to lay down in rest...

709
00:56:57.447 --> 00:57:00.440
..like any other Englishman.

710
00:57:08.825 --> 00:57:15.698
A forlorn and now tragic hope.

711
00:58:29.473 --> 00:58:33.069
He must have lain
back. To rest his head.

712
00:58:35.846 --> 00:58:37.371
Oh. Joseph.

713
00:58:38.749 --> 00:58:40.547
You have your peace now.

714
00:59:09.813 --> 00:59:10.813
What is this?

715
00:59:10.914 --> 00:59:11.914
You may well ask.

716
00:59:11.982 --> 00:59:14.918
I have. this past hour.

717
00:59:15.852 --> 00:59:20.153
come from the grieving
fireside of Frederick Treves.

718
00:59:20.357 --> 00:59:24.727
He is decided on what the
Linklater jury shall now hear from him.

719
00:59:26.496 --> 00:59:30.456
Your sergeant succumbed
to his injuries. Jedediah.

720
00:59:30.667 --> 00:59:32.329
I will not accept that. Fred.

721
00:59:32.536 --> 00:59:35.335
Myself likewise.
Chief Inspector.

722
00:59:35.539 --> 00:59:38.771
Nonetheless. you
shall both do so.

723
00:59:40.744 --> 00:59:46.843
There will be no more talk of
this officer and his role that night.

724
00:59:47.050 --> 00:59:49.212
And you. Edmund.

725
00:59:49.419 --> 00:59:51.684
You will cease all questioning

726
00:59:51.855 --> 00:59:55.724
and suspicion of Inspector
Shine's good name.

727
00:59:55.926 --> 00:59:57.554
You ask the impossible.

728
00:59:57.761 --> 01:00:01.198
You ask me to
wilfully fail in my duty.

729
01:00:01.398 --> 01:00:02.923
You are both too valuable

730
01:00:03.133 --> 01:00:06.467
to the preservation of
peace in this quarter.

731
01:00:06.670 --> 01:00:09.834
And I will not have
that undermined.

732
01:00:13.543 --> 01:00:15.341
The two of you.

733
01:00:15.879 --> 01:00:17.905
You shake hands.

734
01:00:29.693 --> 01:00:31.059
Now!

735
01:00:41.004 --> 01:00:43.130
I take orders from
a man to come here.

736
01:00:43.607 --> 01:00:45.667
I service the needs of
another I call husband.

737
01:00:46.109 --> 01:00:48.738
And there is the man
Duggan who owns me.

738
01:00:48.979 --> 01:00:50.857
Reid. I swear to God if
anything happens to her...

739
01:00:50.881 --> 01:00:53.112
What is it you fear?
What is it you fear?
